Iconic 😌 great ramen and atmosphere
Great bibimbap
Liked Miso ramen. And this place sells Japanese snacks, food, alcohol, and seasoning. So, it’s convenient to buy there.
If you're used to instant ramen than this is decent. If you've ever had ramen from Japan or Mensho or even Katana-ya then you'll be disappointed.
The ramen was a little watery. However, you can buy Japanese tea and Japanese sweets, so if you want to enjoy the taste of Japan, I recommend it.
Nice neighborhood store
Very welcoming place, beautiful ready-to-go plates and sweets ans a nice selection of wines. Glad they survived!
Great local spot!
Excellent customer service.  Will definitely stop back on my next visit to SF.
Really good vegan ramen
Service and variety on food was great
Worst vegetarian  ramen I have ever had. Not worth $15, Gosh!
Delicious vegan ramen, friendly staff, authentic Japanese market options!

Miso style ramen is thick style broth. Pre-made probably the same day. It’s good in a pinch if you live in the neighborhood. They will make to-go orders.  A Fast casual place, you order at checkout counter and wait for food to be delivered. This is more of a grab and go food type of place then sit and enjoy.
Consistently a great value eating experience, never too crowded, good service and good ramen and omusubi
Ramen was a great surprise at this corner store. Delicious and hearty broth. Go and try for yourself to compare!
Delicious ramen and interesting specialty shop
Clean and delicious!!

Nice deli on Polk street, very spacious. They have seating outside and also inside. They have many choices of drink and food items. Staff was reasonably friendly. They did not like me asking my drinks in 'for here' cups, instead they gave me in to go cups!
Great food and service!! Highly recommend.
Great chill spot to get snacks and bites to eat
Nice latte!

Wow! Visiting SF and thrilled we found this little gem on Polk Street! ❤️ Make sure to try the omusubi (rice balls), especially the salmon and the Bibimbop. Delicious, friendly place to hang out while you contemplate where your journey leads you next!
Good ramen

This place serves a solid bowl of ramen in a cute (small) Japanese market.
The pork in miso ramen smells great and tastes great. Noodles were also good. But the flavor of the soup still no really Japanese.

Good place to get a variety of Japanese food.  They serve japanese ramen and other finger foods.  They also have a back market that serves a large selection of sake and japanese craft beer in the back.
Great Matcha Latte, great Black Sesame Latte !!
Bomb Miso Ramen. The pork and Teriyaki Rice Ball was great too.
Common Sage does so many things well from coffee to ramen to high internet speed
Delicious triangles made to order and more
Super Tasty Miso Ramen in a cute shop with no wait during my visit

This place have the best wine and Japanese beer in the area ,the staff is always friendly and professional except for the counter person today theat had a attitude when I asked for soup to go and she want to convince me to take the soup on a coffee cup and I asked for a soup container since I was taking it very far .

Sesame latte is delish. It’s caffeine-free and dairy-free if you get one of the alternative milks. Vegetarian ramen is also pretty tasty! They have lots of little snacks and treats. Try the honey cake!
Awesome local establishment. I love this place.
Small inside area, sort of a weird hybrid of corner market/carryout/eat in. The Common Sage ramen was pretty good, though. Be warned, if you buy alcohol here, you can't consume it on the premises.
Great to stop by and grab ramen, sandwiches, and omusubi. They also have an extensive selection of great sake, wine and beer.
Awesome ramen/rice ball/coffee and Japanese/asian snack place. Everyone there is friendly and helpful. Love the wine collection and some interesting sake too.
Deli store with seating at the back for a quick stop to eat. Ramen miso is the recommended choice from nice staff. Also wifi, room for wheel chairs though it's not ideal. No restroom

Nice surprise this place. It looks they do coffees but surprisingly also ramen as well as a grocery shop full of Japanese goods, good but doesn't seem authentic, there's something different about it, something alternative. Luckily the garlic paste changed everything. I also had a matcha latte. Nice cool and chilled place
Try the chashu (pork) ramen. Ask for extra meat if you're a hungry beast like me!! 😁

I am so happy to have stumbled across this place. They have amazing matcha lattes, black sesame lattes, and other drinks -- but also a ton of super yummy desserts. The Ramen looks amazing, although I haven't tried it yet!
Fun beer selection!
Awesome authentic ramen, big choice of teas, price is very decent for SF
Lovely Japanese restaurant/grocery store with lots of options for onirigi

Love this place and visit often for lunch. Veggie ramen is great and they have an excellent garlic oil you can add to your ramen. Pleasant atmosphere with communal seating that usually isn't crowded. The staff are welcoming and helpful with …
Great ramen !

This is my go to spot to eat every time I fly in San Francisco. Love the food and enjoy the atmosphere.  I did not catch the gentleman's name but he is the one who cooks the ramen and he was so funny and sweet. The food is always fresh and delicious  and YES I will be returning per usual!!!
Solid spot for tea and Japanese goods, didn't try the food but like the space and concept
Its a cute place with unique wines and Japanese snacks
Ramen tastes great, but the portion is small.
Good store to buy Japanese foods or drinks. Good service. But when I go there, items were changed or run out.
Cute Japanese place in the middle of Nob Hill. A bit expensive, but good if you want something authentically japanese vibe

Really enjoyed this place!  Such an eclectic menu - so many tea choices - and a super friendly staff.  They educated me and had me feeling like a regular in no time.  I had a black sesame hot tea with sushi....it was just fabulous!  Casual with bold flavors - just a delight!
Awesome Ramen and very friendly staff

Staffs are very friendly. I ordered Ramen and onigiri combo. I was not hungry, so ramen was half size. Onigiri (mentaiko) was warm! Staff told me, they make onigiri after they took an order. So fresh! But if you are so so or hungry, you should order regular size :)
Friendly staff, great selection of sake, and decent pork ramen. Cute neighborhood market that I hope stays longer than the old blue fog market that was there prior

We dropped off our luggage here with Bagbnb and stopped to have a bite. Really nice place for a quick stop or a sit down meal. The ramen bowl was amazing and very filling and the staff were very helpful to us during our stay!
Great place for ramen and tea. 🍺 selection has some hard to find imports.

Wowzwers. This is seriously the best coffee shop in the city. They've got not just fancy coffee, but also fancy tea, fancy ramen, and fancy beer, sake, etc. They also got some pretty fancy desserts. Go here!
Delicious food. One request to the management, please replace your chopsticks, the narrow end makes it hard to eat ramen with

I absolutely love this place! The Ramen noodle soup is very good, the omusubi are excellent. I love I can get all that food on the go. Pastries are great too.  I do regret that they sell less French food nowadays when they used to sell …

Nice music. Delicious ramen. The garlic and spicy sauces on the tables is ok but ramen might be even better without it. The ramen meat is better than average. Suntory free beer is delicious.
Great ramen, simple seating.
Ramen here is quite delicious! And the drinks are too!
Nice little deli
I had a ramen and a macha. Sometimes they have special menu. you should try it.
Yummy Ramen and good Service

Yummy quick eats.  Even my picky ramen eater of a husband liked it! I've been wanting to check this place out ever since it opened, and I'm sure I'll be back. We both ordered the $9 Common Sage ramen and while it wasn't the tastiest ramen …

Chashu pork sandwich was a bit heavy, but I really enjoy their omusubi  (rice balls). Cheap and small portioned snacks with clean and simple ingredients. Yum! They also have ramen options which you can't find anywhere else on Polk St.

solid comfort ramen on polk! they sell all kinds of wines, sake, specialty drinks including interesting Japanese snacks, desserts and other delicious pastries and coffee. If you're dining in, expect few tables for quick in-out service.

It's a small grocery with some healthful but tasty options for ramen, sandwiches, and rice balls! Also small selection of pastries, Sightglass coffee, and drinks. Lots of sake and other liquor options.

My neighborhood Japanese cafe. Casual eatery with great ramen. Saturdays they usually have vegan ramen. You can call ahead to have the ramen ready. Try their banana bread and match or chai latte. Friendly service!
Good Ramen. Huge sake collection.
I like this store but they just stopped selling their omelette croissant sandwich so I'm disappointed :(

Cool little Asian++ cafe and market. The musubi here are the best small items to nom on, esp the pork. Looks to be the same chashu as what's used in the ramen, meaning you get a nice slice of hot pork in your rice ball!

Had the Cha Shu Ramen, broth had no depth of flavor, and noodles were factory made and simply warmed up from a freezer. Employees working were nice, but it took far too long for our ramen to come out. Being a frequent traveler to Japan...I know how ramen should taste and this place is a sorry disappointment.

Ramen is delicious and filling for both body and soul. Common Sage is the Hapa love and intersectional culture Nob Hill needs. Considering there are no ramen places nearby unless you go to Japan Town, this is a true gem. Replete with a …
Really great home made ramen & a wonderful variety of rice balls. Tell Marlo I sent you!

SUPER cute little store on the corner. I never really noticed it was there until I looked for today in search of a sandwich. I thought their turkey sandwich was pretty average, but I really liked the cheese. I also got a salmon rice ball, …

The ramen here is SO GOOD! The noodles taste a little buttery and the broth is savory. The Cha-syu Miso-Ramen has double pork which is perfect for super hungry nights (I get the Common Sage Miso-Ramen when I'm not as hungry). Corey has …
Soooo Goood. And oh the Japanese snacks. Oh the Japanese snacks!
Lovely corner bistro with great Miso Ramen and included mini shop. Decent prices and friendly staff.
Amazing musubi. Asian sandwich is awesome as well. Pretty much everything on the menu is delicious.  Nice folks too.
Beautiful place with kind owners, worth a visit :)

First!!! Great atmosphere and top notch ice coffee.  Seems like a Japanese European fusion with things like made to order sushi balls and same to freshly baked bread and quality cheese selection.  Only issue is lack of seating and high prices.
